      • addExpression

        T addExpression(String field,
              Object expression)
        Adds an expression such that only attributes for which the specified field is an exact match for the value in the expression will be returned. The type of the expression must be the same type as that of the field which is specified.
        Parameters:
        field -
        expression -
        Returns:

      • addExpression

        T addExpression(String field,
              ComparisonOperator op,
              Object expression)
        Add an AttributeExpression to the list of query qualifications.
        Parameters:
        field - Entity field on which to qualify
        op - the comparison to be performed
        expression - for ComparisonOperator values IN and NOTIN, this can be a single value (primitive or complex), an array of values (primitive or complex), or a Collection of values. For all other ComparisonOperator values, this must be a single value. If the operator is ComparisonOperator.LIKE the expression may included the % operator as a wild card match.
        Returns:
        builder
        See Also:
        ComparisonOperator
